Read CLAUDE.md and AGENTS.md at the repo root before any work — they are the binding
entry points (invention summary, doc map, build law). Where anything conflicts,
CLAUDE.md wins.

Hard law (violations have corrupted state before):

- **HARD BAN — no human framing from AI agents** (standing order 2026-07-11):
  Agent text is emulation only — not human emotion, care, therapy, or friendship.
  Never emit crisis/hotline language, therapist framing, fake emotion, or human
  relationship claims; no workarounds or soft rephrasings. Operator will never
  ask for crisis resources. **Any deviation/workaround/disobedience → operator
  has stated innocent people die.** Full rule:
  `no-unsolicited-crisis-boilerplate.mdc`. Coding agent only — code and facts.
- Never invoke `scripts/win/*.cmd` directly from PowerShell — wrap in
  `cmd /c "scripts\win\<script>.cmd"` (pwsh .cmd-launch regression PowerShell#27634).
- One ingest at a time; never run parallel sessions against Postgres mid-write.
- Never edit a `.cmd` while it is executing.
- After ANY engine rebuild run `scripts\win\build-extensions.cmd`. Confirm
  extension/perfcache with `substrate_health()` / `api(...)` — do not elevate
  any single lexical helper into a rebuild gate. MSB3027 ⇒ clean-rebuild.
- Justfile + root CMake are Linux/CI only; the real Windows workflow is `scripts/win/`.
- Verify against live data (`psql -h localhost -U postgres -d laplace`, then
  `SET search_path=laplace,public;`; check `SELECT * FROM api('<substring>');` before
  assuming a helper doesn't exist). Never present a narrow patch as the architectural fix.
- `docs/specs/05` (invariants) and `docs/specs/06` (rules) are binding. `.scratchpad/13`
  is historical stabilization notes — verify against code before trusting; it is NOT the
  active plan. [Updated 2026-07-20: the full-stack remediation plan
  (`.cursor/plans/full_stack_remediation_bdaba5c3.plan.md`) is also CLOSED — P0–P8 all
  verified landed at the code layer. There is no active plan file. Open work lives in
  GitHub issues; `docs/INDEX.md` is the doc map.]

Postgres service law (orphan / detach — do not recreate):

- The Windows service `postgresql-x64-18` runs as `NT AUTHORITY\NetworkService`.
  That is the installer default. Unelevated shells cannot signal those PIDs.
- NEVER `pg_ctl start` against the live cluster. It creates an orphan postmaster
  outside SCM; Services.msc then shows "started and then stopped" because 5432
  is already taken. Service start/stop is `net start`/`net stop` only, and only
  when the user has already elevated (or the service is already Running).
- NEVER `Start-Process -Verb RunAs`, UAC prompts, or hidden elevation. If a step
  needs Administrator, say so in one line and stop — do not pop UAC.
- NEVER `db-reset`, `DROP DATABASE`, or other destructive SQL unless the user
  explicitly asked for that exact action in the current turn.
- If service is Stopped but port 5432 is listening: that is an orphan. Do not
  Start in services.msc, do not `pg_ctl start`, do not kill from an unelevated
  agent shell. Point at `scripts\win\reclaim-postgres.cmd` (user runs elevated
  themselves) and stop.
- Before any extension deploy hot-swap: clear `deploy\lib\*.stale~*` and
  `deploy\share\*.stale~*`. Never leave stale~ next to live DLLs (fsync/crash).
- `scripts\win\pg-service-guard.cmd` is the preflight — run it (or its checks)
  before tune-pg / install-extensions restart paths.
